    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n(This has been requested several times but I couldn't find an existing issue in neovim/vim/`todo.txt`.)\n\nScripts can't read or set the dot-repeat (.) \"register).\n\nUse-cases:\n- Because prompt-buffer inserts/edits set the dot register, plugins like telescope may want to restore it, since typically those edits are throwaway and aren't intended to be repeated.\n    - #33024\n- Ability to read the dot-repeat register may help plugins like https://github.com/tpope/vim-repeat or multicursor plugins.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nScripts can read the last dot-repeat operation.\n\nScripts can set the dot-repeat register, then `.` will execute that code.\n\nNote: work on multicursor may introduce a more elaborate API for getting the \"history\" of edits.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Ability to read the dot-repeat register\n\nCurrently It can be read but only after you leave insert mode the value is updated, also pure normal mode modification like \"dw\" will not change previous insert mode dot register content (what have typed) via `vim.fn.getreg(\".\")`.\n\nI guess `vim.fn.getreg(\".\")` is the same as `i_CTRL-A` under the hood.",
